<bioghist altrender="history" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Historical Note</head>
<p>
The State Traffic Commission was established July 1, 1935, per 1935 Cum. Suppl. sec. 73c, and administratively under the Highway Dept. In 1977, per P.A. 77-614, the Traffic Commission was transferred to the Dept. of Transportation. The Commission was established as the legal traffic authority of Connecticut, 
to provide rules and regulations for the establishment of uniform traffic control signals, devices, signs, and markings for the use of vehicular and pedestrian traffic upon the public highway.
</p>
	<p>See also the <extptr linktype="simple" href="http://www.cslib.org/agencies/trafficcommission.htm" show="replace" actuate="onrequest" title="State Traffic Commission Agency History"/>.</p>

</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Content</head>
	<p>These records consist solely of meeting agendas and minutes, 1935-1995.</p>
</scopecontent>

<arrangement encodinganalog="351$b" id="a5">
	<head>Arrangement</head>
	<p>The meeting agendas and minutes are arranged chronologically.</p>
</arrangement>

